And human behavior appears to
be environmentally determined.


964
0:55:16,76 --> 0:55:21,54
Meaning, if you were raised by
the Seminole Indians as a baby


965
0:55:21,54 --> 0:55:25,46
never saw anything else, you'd
hold that value system.


966
0:55:25,46 --> 0:55:30,29
And this goes for nations, it goes
for individuals, for families.


967
0:55:30,29 --> 0:55:34,66
They try to indoctrinate their
children to their particular faith


968
0:55:34,66 --> 0:55:39,28
and their country and make them
feel like they're part of that.


969
0:55:39,28 --> 0:55:44,35
And they build a society,
which they call established.


970
0:55:44,35 --> 0:55:49,36
They established a workable point of
view and tend to perpetuate that.


971
0:55:49,36 --> 0:55:54,93
Whereas, all societies are really
emergent, not established.


972
0:55:54,93 --> 0:55:58,2
And so they fight new ideas


973
0:55:58,2 --> 0:56:1,95
that would interfere
with the establishment.


974
0:56:1,95 --> 0:56:6,79
Governments try to perpetuate
that which keeps them in power.


975
0:56:6,79 --> 0:56:11,86
People are not elected to political
office to change things.


976
0:56:11,86 --> 0:56:15,66
They are put there to keep
things the way they are.


977
0:56:15,66 --> 0:56:20,0
So you see, the basis of
corruption is in our society.


978
0:56:20,0 --> 0:56:24,79
Let me make it clear.
All nations then are basically corrupt


979
0:56:24,79 --> 0:56:28,52
because they tend to uphold
existing institutions.


980
0:56:28,52 --> 0:56:32,2
I don't mean to uphold
or downgrade all nations


981
0:56:32,2 --> 0:56:36,79
but communism, socialism, fascism,
the free enterprise-system


982
0:56:36,79 --> 0:56:40,49
and all other sub-cultures
are the same.


983
0:56:40,49 --> 0:56:45,0
They are all basically corrupt.


984
0:56:45,0 --> 0:56:48,53
-The most fundamental characteristic
of our social institutions


985
0:56:48,53 --> 0:56:51,64
is the necessity for
self-preservation.


986
0:56:51,64 --> 0:56:55,45
Whether dealing with a corporation,
a religion or a government


987
0:56:55,45 --> 0:56:59,4
the foremost interest is to
preserve the institution itself.


988
0:56:59,4 --> 0:57:2,53
For instance, the last thing
an oil company would ever want


989
0:57:2,53 --> 0:57:6,48
is the utilization of energy
that was outside of its control.


990
0:57:6,48 --> 0:57:10,6
For it makes that company
less relevant to society.


991
0:57:10,6 --> 0:57:13,61
Likewise the Cold War and the
collapse of the Soviet Union


992
0:57:13,61 --> 0:57:17,35
was, in reality, a way to
preserve and perpetuate


993
0:57:17,35 --> 0:57:23,43
the established economic and global
hegemony of the United States.


994
0:57:23,43 --> 0:57:25,73
Similarly, religions
condition people


995
0:57:25,73 --> 0:57:28,3
to feel guilty for
natural inclinations


996
0:57:28,3 --> 0:57:33,28
each claiming to offer the only
path to forgiveness and salvation.


997
0:57:33,28 --> 0:57:36,32
At the heart of this
institutional self-preservation


998
0:57:36,32 --> 0:57:38,46
lies the monetary system


999
0:57:38,46 --> 0:57:43,32
for it is money that provides the
means for power and survival.


1000
0:57:43,32 --> 0:57:45,19
Therefore, just as a poor person


1001
0:57:45,19 --> 0:57:47,72
might be forced to steal
in order to survive


1002
0:57:47,72 --> 0:57:50,89
it is a natural inclination
to do whatever is needed


1003
0:57:50,89 --> 0:57:53,76
to continue an institution's
profitability.


1004
0:57:53,76 --> 0:57:55,87
This makes it
inherently difficult


1005
0:57:55,87 --> 0:58:0,8
for profit-based institutions to
change, for it puts in jeopardy


1006
0:58:0,8 --> 0:58:2,73
not only the survival of
large groups of people


1007
0:58:2,73 --> 0:58:5,49
but also the coveted
materialistic lifestyles


1008
0:58:5,49 --> 0:58:9,9
associated with
affluence and power.


1009
0:58:9,9 --> 0:58:12,78
Therefore, the paralyzing necessity
to preserve an institution


1010
0:58:12,78 --> 0:58:15,0
regardless of its
social relevance


1011
0:58:15,0 --> 0:58:21,0
is largely rooted in the
need for money or profit.


1012
0:58:21,0 --> 0:58:23,88
[ Industry ]


1013
0:58:23,88 --> 0:58:28,27
- "What's in it for me?
" is the way people think.


1014
0:58:28,27 --> 0:58:31,82
And so if a man makes money
selling a certain product


1015
0:58:31,82 --> 0:58:35,85
that's where he's going to fight
the existence of another product


1016
0:58:35,85 --> 0:58:39,94
that may threaten
his institution.


1017
0:58:39,94 --> 0:58:43,3
Therefore, people
cannot be fair.


1018
0:58:43,3 --> 0:58:45,33
And people do not
trust each other.


1019
0:58:45,33 --> 0:58:47,11
A guy will come
over to you and say


1020
0:58:47,11 --> 0:58:50,5
"I've got just the house you're looking for.
" He's a salesman.


1021
0:58:50,5 --> 0:58:53,74
When a doctor says, "I think
your kidney has to come out."


1022
0:58:53,74 --> 0:58:56,69
I don't know if he's
trying to pay off a yacht


1023
0:58:56,69 --> 0:58:58,67
or that my kidney
has to come out.


1024
0:58:58,67 --> 0:59:3,275
It's hard in a monetary
system to trust people.


1025
0:59:3,275 --> 0:59:6,72
If you came into my store and I
said, "This lamp that I've got


1026
0:59:6,72 --> 0:59:10,4
is pretty good, but the lamp
next door is much better."


1027
0:59:10,4 --> 0:59:13,28
I wouldn't be in business very long.
It wouldn't work.


1028
0:59:13,28 --> 0:59:16,62
If I were ethical,
it wouldn't work.


1029
0:59:16,62 --> 0:59:21,6
So when you say industry cares
for people, that's not true.


1030
0:59:21,6 --> 0:59:24,12
They can't afford to be ethical.


1031
0:59:24,12 --> 0:59:28,61
So your system is not designed to
serve the well-being of people.


1032
0:59:28,61 --> 0:59:33,96
If you still don't understand that
there would be no outsourcing of jobs


1033
0:59:33,96 --> 0:59:35,98
if they cared about people.


1034
0:59:35,98 --> 0:59:38,48
Industry does not care.
They only hire people


1035
0:59:38,48 --> 0:59:42,4
because it hasn't
been automated yet.


1036
0:59:42,4 --> 0:59:45,15
So don't talk about
decency and ethics.


1037
0:59:45,15 --> 0:59:49,77
We cannot afford it and
remain in business.


1038
0:59:49,77 --> 0:59:53,82
-It is important to point out that
regardless of the social system -


1039
0:59:53,82 --> 0:59:57,9
whether fascist, socialist,
capitalist or communist


1040
0:59:57,9 --> 1:0:3,409
the underlying mechanism is still
money, labor and competition.


1041
1:0:3,409 --> 1:0:7,718
Communist China is no less
capitalistic than the United States.


1042
1:0:7,718 --> 1:0:9,36
The only difference
is the degree


1043
1:0:9,36 --> 1:0:13,2
by which the state
intervenes in enterprise.


1044
1:0:13,2 --> 1:0:16,53
The reality is that
"Monetary-ism", so to speak


1045
1:0:16,53 --> 1:0:19,3
is the true mechanism
that guides the interests


1046
1:0:19,3 --> 1:0:22,11
of all the countries
on the planet.


1047
1:0:22,11 --> 1:0:24,35
The most aggressive and
hence dominant variation


1048
1:0:24,35 --> 1:0:28,5
of this monetary-ism is the
free enterprise system.


1049
1:0:28,5 --> 1:0:30,472
The fundamental
perspective, as put forth


1050
1:0:30,472 --> 1:0:34,5
by early free market
economists like Adam Smith


1051
1:0:34,5 --> 1:0:38,44
is that self interest and competition
leads to social prosperity


1052
1:0:38,44 --> 1:0:41,7
as the act of competition
creates incentive


1053
1:0:41,7 --> 1:0:45,3
which motivates
people to persevere.


1054
1:0:45,3 --> 1:0:49,541
However, what isn't talked about,
is how a competition based economy


1055
1:0:49,541 --> 1:0:52,42
invariably leads to
strategic corruption


1056
1:0:52,42 --> 1:0:56,464
power and wealth consolidation,
social stratification


1057
1:0:56,464 --> 1:1:2,34
technological paralysis, labor
abuse and ultimately a covert form


1058
1:1:2,34 --> 1:1:7,8
of government dictatorship
by the rich elite.


1059
1:1:7,8 --> 1:1:12,0
The word "corruption" is often
defined as moral perversion.


1060
1:1:12,0 --> 1:1:15,8
If a company dumps toxic waste
into the ocean to save money


1061
1:1:15,8 --> 1:1:19,94
most people recognize this
as "corrupt behavior".


1062
1:1:19,94 --> 1:1:23,82
On a more subtle level, when
Walmart moves into a small town


1063
1:1:23,82 --> 1:1:26,436
and forces small
businesses to shut down


1064
1:1:26,436 --> 1:1:30,5
for they are unable to compete,
a grey area emerges.


1065
1:1:30,5 --> 1:1:33,29
For what exactly is
Walmart doing wrong?


1066
1:1:33,29 --> 1:1:37,52
Why should they care about the Mom
and Pop organizations they destroy?


1067
1:1:37,52 --> 1:1:41,8
Yet, even more subtly, when a
person gets fired from their job


1068
1:1:41,8 --> 1:1:44,11
because a new machine
has been created


1069
1:1:44,11 --> 1:1:46,33
which can do the
work for less money


1070
1:1:46,33 --> 1:1:49,885
people tend to just accept
that as "the way it is"


1071
1:1:49,885 --> 1:1:49,905
.


1072
1:1:49,905 --> 1:1:55,53
not seeing the inherent corrupt
inhumanity of such an action.


1073
1:1:55,53 --> 1:1:59,44
Because the fact is, whether
it is dumping toxic waste


1074
1:1:59,44 --> 1:2:3,32
having a monopoly enterprise
or downsizing the workforce


1075
1:2:3,32 --> 1:2:6,939
the motive is the same: Profit.


1076
1:2:6,939 --> 1:2:6,94
.


1077
1:2:6,94 --> 1:2:11,2
They are all different degrees of
the same self-preserving mechanism


1078
1:2:11,2 --> 1:2:16,42
which always puts the well-being
of people second to monetary gain.


1079
1:2:16,42 --> 1:2:21,93
Therefore, corruption is not
some byproduct of monetary-ism


1080
1:2:21,93 --> 1:2:24,96
it is the very foundation.


1081
1:2:24,96 --> 1:2:27,2
And while most people
acknowledge this tendency


1082
1:2:27,2 --> 1:2:30,557
on one level or another,
the majority remains naive


1083
1:2:30,557 --> 1:2:32,93
as to the broad ramifications


1084
1:2:32,93 --> 1:2:35,545
of having such a
selfish mechanism


1085
1:2:35,545 --> 1:2:38,576
as the guiding
mentality in society.


1086
1:2:38,576 --> 1:2:40,2
-Internal documents show


1087
1:2:40,2 --> 1:2:43,69
that after this company
positively absolutely knew


1088
1:2:43,69 --> 1:2:46,831
that they had a medication that
was infected with the AIDS virus


1089
1:2:46,831 --> 1:2:49,23
they took the product off
the market in the US


1090
1:2:49,23 --> 1:2:52,34
and then they dumped it in France,
Europe, Asia and Latin America.


1091
1:2:52,34 --> 1:2:54,85
The US government
allowed it to happen.


1092
1:2:54,85 --> 1:2:57,15
The FDA allowed this to happen


1093
1:2:57,15 --> 1:2:59,9
and now the government is
completely looking the other way.


1094
1:2:59,9 --> 1:3:4,96
Thousands of innocent hemophiliacs
have died from the AIDS virus.


1095
1:3:4,96 --> 1:3:8,38
This company knew absolutely
that it was infected with AIDS,


1096
1:3:8,38 --> 1:3:15,4
they dumped it because they wanted
to turn this disaster into a profit.


1097
1:3:15,4 --> 1:3:19,14
-So you see, you have
built-in corruption.


1098
1:3:19,14 --> 1:3:21,54
We're all chiseling
off each other


1099
1:3:21,54 --> 1:3:26,302
and you can't expect decency
or that sort of thing.


1100
1:3:26,302 --> 1:3:28,73
Politics


1101
1:3:28,73 --> 1:3:32,0
...a feeling that they
don't know who to elect.


1102
1:3:32,0 --> 1:3:34,24
They think in terms
of a democracy


1103
1:3:34,24 --> 1:3:39,0
which is not possible in a
monetary based economy.


1104
1:3:39,0 --> 1:3:42,68
If you have more money to
advertise your position


1105
1:3:42,68 --> 1:3:46,749
the position you desire in
government, that isn't a democracy.


1106
1:3:46,749 --> 1:3:46,75
.


1107
1:3:46,75 --> 1:3:51,46
It serves those in positions
of differential advantage.


1108
1:3:51,46 --> 1:3:56,519
So it's always a dictatorship of the
elitist, the financially wealthy.


1109
1:3:56,519 --> 1:3:56,9
.


1110
1:3:56,9 --> 1:3:59,35
"We can either have democracy
in this country or


1111
1:3:59,35 --> 1:4:2,25
we can have great wealth
concentrated in the hands of a few,


1112
1:4:2,25 --> 1:4:4,728
but we can't have both."
- Louis Brandeis - Supreme Court Justice


1113
1:4:4,728 --> 1:4:6,74
-It is an interesting
observation


1114
1:4:6,74 --> 1:4:9,9
to note how seemingly
unknown personalities


1115
1:4:9,9 --> 1:4:13,71
magically appear on the scene
as presidential candidates.


1116
1:4:13,71 --> 1:4:16,5
Then before you know it,
somehow you are left to choose


1117
1:4:16,5 --> 1:4:19,98
from a small group of
extremely wealthy people


1118
1:4:19,98 --> 1:4:24,73
who suspiciously have the
same broad social view.


1119
1:4:24,73 --> 1:4:26,72
Obviously it's a joke.


1120
1:4:26,72 --> 1:4:28,89
The people placed on
the ballot are done so


1121
1:4:28,89 --> 1:4:32,7
because they have been
pre-decided to be acceptable


1122
1:4:32,7 --> 1:4:37,33
by the established financial
powers who actually run the show.


1123
1:4:37,33 --> 1:4:41,98
Yet many who understand this
illusion of democracy, often think


1124
1:4:41,98 --> 1:4:46,83
"If only we could just get our honest,
ethical politicians in power,


1125
1:4:46,83 --> 1:4:48,95
then we would be okay".


1126
1:4:48,95 --> 1:4:51,74
Well, while this idea, of
course, seems reasonable


1127
1:4:51,74 --> 1:4:55,9
in our established
oriented world view


1128
1:4:55,9 --> 1:4:59,24
it is unfortunately
another fallacy.


1129
1:4:59,24 --> 1:5:3,112
For when it really comes down
to what is actually important,


1130
1:5:3,112 --> 1:5:7,39
the institution of politics and
thus politicians themselves


1131
1:5:7,39 --> 1:5:10,79
have absolutely no
true relevance as to


1132
1:5:10,79 --> 1:5:14,815
what makes our world
and society function.


1133
1:5:14,815 --> 1:5:18,12
-It's not politicians
that can solve problems.


1134
1:5:18,12 --> 1:5:20,85
They have no technical
capabilities.


1135
1:5:20,85 --> 1:5:23,12
They don't know how
to solve problems.


1136
1:5:23,12 --> 1:5:27,13
Even if they were sincere, they
don't know how to solve problems.


1137
1:5:27,13 --> 1:5:32,15
It's the technicians that produce
the desalinization plants.


1138
1:5:32,15 --> 1:5:34,77
It's the technicians that
give you electricity.


1139
1:5:34,77 --> 1:5:36,5
That give you motor vehicles.


1140
1:5:36,5 --> 1:5:39,4
That heat your house and
cool it in the summer time.


1141
1:5:39,4 --> 1:5:43,37
It's technology that solves
problems, not politics.


1142
1:5:43,37 --> 1:5:49,4
Politics cannot solve problems 'cause
they are not trained to do so.


1143
1:5:49,4 --> 1:5:52,25
-Very few people today
stop and consider


1144
1:5:52,25 --> 1:5:55,72
what it is that actually
improves their lives.


1145
1:5:55,72 --> 1:5:58,5
Is it money? Obviously not.


1146
1:5:58,5 --> 1:6:3,2
One cannot eat money or stuff money
into their car to get it to run.


1147
1:6:3,2 --> 1:6:5,36
Is it politics?


1148
1:6:5,36 --> 1:6:8,3
All politicians can
do is create laws


1149
1:6:8,3 --> 1:6:11,45
establish budgets
and declare war.


1150
1:6:11,45 --> 1:6:13,69
Is it religion? Of course not.


1151
1:6:13,69 --> 1:6:15,91
Religion creates nothing except


1152
1:6:15,91 --> 1:6:19,85
intangible emotional solace
for those who require it.


1153
1:6:19,85 --> 1:6:23,78
The true gift that we
as human beings have


1154
1:6:23,78 --> 1:6:26,73
which has been solely
responsible for everything


1155
1:6:26,73 --> 1:6:29,0
that has improved our lives


1156
1:6:29,0 --> 1:6:31,79
is technology.


1157
1:6:31,79 --> 1:6:33,53
What is technology?


1158
1:6:33,53 --> 1:6:35,4
Technology is a pencil


1159
1:6:35,4 --> 1:6:39,44
which allows one to solidify ideas
on paper for communication.


1160
1:6:39,44 --> 1:6:43,14
Technology is an automobile, which
allows one to travel faster


1161
1:6:43,14 --> 1:6:44,78
than feet would allow.


1162
1:6:44,78 --> 1:6:47,35
Technology is a
pair of eye glasses


1163
1:6:47,35 --> 1:6:50,9
which enables sight for
those who need it.


1164
1:6:50,9 --> 1:6:56,43
Applied technology itself is merely
an extension of human attributes


1165
1:6:56,43 --> 1:6:58,469
which reduces human effort


1166
1:6:58,469 --> 1:7:1,97
freeing humans from a
particular chore or problem.


1167
1:7:1,97 --> 1:7:4,6
Imagine what your life
would be like today


1168
1:7:4,6 --> 1:7:6,9
without a telephone, or an oven


1169
1:7:6,9 --> 1:7:9,6
or a computer, or an airplane.


1170
1:7:9,6 --> 1:7:9,64
.


1171
1:7:9,64 --> 1:7:12,375
And, everything in your home,
which you take for granted


1172
1:7:12,375 --> 1:7:14,415
from a doorbell, to a table


1173
1:7:14,415 --> 1:7:17,58
to a dishwasher, is technology


1174
1:7:17,58 --> 1:7:23,4
generated from the creative scientific
ingenuity of human technicians.


1175
1:7:23,4 --> 1:7:26,69
Not money, politics or religion.


1176
1:7:26,69 --> 1:7:30,39
These are false institutions.


1177
1:7:30,39 --> 1:7:33,63
- ...and writing your
congressman is fantastic.


1178
1:7:33,63 --> 1:7:36,85
They tell you to write your congressman
if you want something done.


1179
1:7:36,85 --> 1:7:40,72
The men in Washington should be
at the forefront of technology.


1180
1:7:40,72 --> 1:7:42,74
The forefront of human study.


1181
1:7:42,74 --> 1:7:44,6
The forefront of crime.


1182
1:7:44,6 --> 1:7:47,4
All the factors that
shape human behavior.


1183
1:7:47,4 --> 1:7:49,4
You don't have to write
your congressman.


1184
1:7:49,4 --> 1:7:54,1
What kind of people are they that
are appointed to do that job?


1185
1:7:54,1 --> 1:7:57,1
The future will have
great difficulty...


1186
1:7:57,1 --> 1:8:0,66
and the question that's
raised by politicians is:


1187
1:8:0,66 --> 1:8:3,1
How much will a project cost?


1188
1:8:3,1 --> 1:8:6,1
The question is not "how
much will it cost".


1189
1:8:6,1 --> 1:8:8,5
Do we have the resources?


1190
1:8:8,5 --> 1:8:12,55
And we have the resources
today to house everyone,


1191
1:8:12,55 --> 1:8:15,34
build hospitals all
over the world,


1192
1:8:15,34 --> 1:8:17,54
build schools all over the world


1193
1:8:17,54 --> 1:8:22,96
the finest equipment in labs for
teaching and doing medical research.


1194
1:8:22,96 --> 1:8:27,37
So you see, we have all that,
but we're in a monetary system


1195
1:8:27,37 --> 1:8:32,15
and in a monetary
system there's profit.


1196
1:8:32,15 --> 1:8:35,915
-And what is the fundamental mechanism
that drives the profit system


1197
1:8:35,915 --> 1:8:37,92
besides self-interest?


1198
1:8:37,92 --> 1:8:41,87
What is it exactly that maintains
that competitive edge at its core?


1199
1:8:41,87 --> 1:8:45,56
Is it high efficiency
and sustainability?


1200
1:8:45,56 --> 1:8:48,888
No. That isn't part
of their design.


